timeline.bodyText:
Not pressing and also a thing to consider for other cloud vendors too...
       // GCP VPCs are global. Subnets have a global scope in region. So picking the first availability zone in the region for subnet. String zone = compute.regions().get(projectId, region.value()).execute().getZones().stream().findFirst().orElse(null);
We chose the first AZs in the region list to host the compute resources. If they talk to the database hosted in multiple AZs and if the traffic goes to a different AZ then the customer incurs a cost of 1 US cent per GB. Is it possible to pick AZs for database is in such a way that it is co-located with compute for the primary and the secondary can be any other AZ?

